
ATTENTION: Read game-README first !!!

NOTE: In 0.3.2 version of OSRPG Map Editor 0.3 corresponds to OMF 0.3 (highest
supported format version), and 2 to Editor enchancements (around the format)

---------------------------------------------------------------------
Notes for Windows users
---------------------------------------------------------------------

You must create HOME environment variable, that one should point to your
home directory (e.g., C:/Documents and Settings/root).
ATTENTION: path must be with FORWARD slash (UNIX style), NOT BACKWARD slash!
And WITHOUT ENDING slash!

You can set environment variables in MyComputer->Advanced->EnvironmentVariables

---------------------------------------------------------------------
Notes for all users
---------------------------------------------------------------------

Inside your home directory you must create such directory structure:

$(HOME)/.config/osrpg/editor/

and place there file named exactly as "settings"
There you must write the path to data directory in the way:

DATA_DIR=path/to/data/directory/

It's most likely should point to maggun project's data directory.
For my system the file

$(HOME)/.config/osrpg/editor/settings

contains:

DATA_DIR=/home/kornerr/OSRPG/branches/maggun/data/

(ENDING slash is obligatory!)

---------------------------------------------------------------------
Requirements
---------------------------------------------------------------------

Irrlicht SVN revision 267 to be able to compile

